text: Faristenia atrimaculata is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It is found in Korea.Faristenia at funet The wingspan is 14–16 mm. The forewings are greyish orange, partly irrorated with dark brown scales and with a large, trapezoidal costal patch. The hindwings are pale grey.Insecta koreana 10 : 36 ==References== Category:Faristenia Category:Moths described in 1993
title: Faristenia atrimaculata
